snippet: The clash revived tensions in the Serb-controlled area, where Kosovo Serbs set up roadblocks last year to stop the ethnic Albanian government from extending control over the region.
abstract: Nato-led peacekeepers clash with Serb protesters seeking to prevent international troops from removing their roadblocks in northern Kosovo; at least six people are injured.
lead_paragraph: The clash revived tensions in the Serb-controlled area, where Kosovo Serbs set up roadblocks last year to stop the ethnic Albanian government from extending control over the region.
